<section class="seo-faq">
<div class="faq-container">

<h2>Frequently Asked Questions – Website Development Cost in India</h2>

<div class="faq-item">
<h3>How much does a website cost in India?</h3>
<p>A professional website in India typically costs between ₹15,000 and ₹50,000 depending on the number of pages, design complexity, and features like ecommerce, SEO setup, and integrations.</p>
</div>

<div class="faq-item">
<h3>What factors affect website development cost?</h3>
<p>The main factors include website type, number of pages, UI/UX design level, CMS requirements, SEO setup, payment gateway integration, and automation tools.</p>
</div>

<div class="faq-item">
<h3>How long does it take to build a website?</h3>
<p>A landing page can be developed within 5–7 days, while a business website may take 10–15 days. Ecommerce websites typically require 3–4 weeks depending on features.</p>
</div>

<div class="faq-item">
<h3>Is SEO included in website development?</h3>
<p>Basic SEO setup such as meta tags, Google Search Console integration, and analytics tracking is usually included. Advanced SEO services are optional.</p>
</div>

<div class="faq-item">
<h3>Do small businesses really need a website?</h3>
<p>Yes. A website helps businesses appear on Google search results, build credibility, capture leads, and reach customers beyond social media platforms.</p>
</div>

</div>
</section>

